A handwritten note thanking them for ` taking her home safely ' has gone viral , just a week after the Germanwings tragedy that claimed 150 lives .
A screenshot of the letter was shared on Twitter , and in a matter of minutes amassed more than 2,000 shares .
The heartfelt message was posted by airline pilot Jai Dillon , who was shown the A4 by a colleague in the industry .
The letter has over 3,700 shares and has been 3,000 times .